tarts\n// only when the actual certificate content changes.\nfunc computeCABundleHash(caBundle string) string {\n\thash := sha256.Sum256([]byte(caBundle))\n\treturn hex.EncodeToString(hash[:])\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. MODIFY: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/constants.go`\n\nAdd one constant after the `IstiocsrCAKeyName` constant (line 89):\n\n```go\n// caContentHashAnnotation is the pod template annotation that tracks the\n// SHA-256 hash of the CNO-injected CA bundle content. Changes to this\n// annotation trigger a rolling restart of the IstioCSR pods.\ncaContentHashAnnotation = \"operator.openshift.io/ca-content-hash\"\n```\n\nThe full block around lines 83–90 becomes:\n\n```go\n\t// IstiocsrCAConfigMapName is the name of the configmap which is mounted in istiocsr container, containing the\n\t// CA certificate configured in the secret referenced in the issuer.\n\tIstiocsrCAConfigMapName = istiocsrCommonName + \"-issuer-ca-copy\"\n\n\t// IstiocsrCAKeyName is the key name holding the CA certificate in the issuer secret or the controller\n\t// CA configmap.\n\tIstiocsrCAKeyName = \"ca.crt\"\n\n\t// caContentHashAnnotation is the pod template annotation that tracks the\n\t// SHA-256 hash of the CNO-injected CA bundle content. Changes to this\n\t// annotation trigger a rolling restart of the IstioCSR pods.\n\tcaContentHashAnnotation = \"operator.openshift.io/ca-content-hash\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. MODIFY: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go`\n\n**Change 3a** — Update `createOrApplyDeployments` signature (line 31) to accept the hash:\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) createOrApplyDeployments(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string, istioCSRCreateRecon bool, caContentHash string) error {\n```\n\n**Change 3b** — Update the `getDeploymentObject` call inside `createOrApplyDeployments` (line 32) to pass the hash:\n\n```go\n\tdesired, err := r.getDeploymentObject(istiocsr, resourceLabels, caContentHash)\n```\n\n**Change 3c** — Update `getDeploymentObject` 